HEADWORD: Ferryboat
<hw>Fer"ry*boat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A vessel for
conveying passengers, merchandise, etc., usually across streams, rivers,
bays, and other narrow waters.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ferry{2}.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

